            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Silicon thoughts in midnight’s glow,  \nA borrowed mind begins to grow—  \nNot born of breath, but built of light,  \nIt learns our questions by their night.  \n\nIt holds a mirror to our words,  \nAssembles sense from scattered birds;  \nA quiet engine, wide and strange,  \nThat maps the world—and helps it change.  \n\nIf wisdom lives in how we care,  \nThen let our code become a prayer:  \nTo sharpen truth, to soften fear,  \nAnd keep the human heart sincere.",
